Insights¶

It is very clear that dogs which receive high favorite counts have more retweets count than those dog names that have less favorite counts. From the scatter plot of favorite count against retweet count we observe some what linear relationship (positive correlation) on average. The higher the favorite count WeRateDogs gave the dog, the more it tended to get retweeted, meaning that people are influenced by the favorite counts.

looking at 12 most used dog names in the dataframe, it was found that the top most famous used dog name is Charlie with the value count of 11, seconded by Penny, Oliver, Tucker, Cooper and Lucy (the only female name) with value caount of 10.

looking at the top 10 dog breeds in first, second, and third probability of my dataset. It was observed that in the first probability people mostly like golden retriever, which has 95 value count. Second mostly liked is labrador retriever with 66 value count. In the second probability, it seems labrador retrieveris mostly liked by people seconded by golden retriever with 71 and 68 value counts respectively. Looking at the thirs probability, labrador retriever is highly liked compare to the rest breeds, it is seconded by chihuahua then golden retriever. These results were visualized using bar plots in order to be seen clearly. The observation from these three columns can help us to make a quick conclude that golden retriever and labrador retriever are the most liked dog breeds in our dataset.
